narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Definitely. If you're at all interested in the topic, you should take it. The readings are manageable and really fascinating. The professor is nice. You'll learn a tremendous amount about American history and be exposed to a lot of interesting ideas. As a senior I can say this was one of the best seminars I've taken at Yale.
Take this course. Gives you a great overview of Religion's role in America.
I absolutely would. I learned an incredible amount and it has changed how I view American history.
I would recommend the class, because it treats an important feature not only of history, but also of contemporary American politics.
